up}}\n\n[[Brighton & Hove Albion]] were knocked out of the [[Football League Cup]] in the first round by [[EFL Championship|Championship]] side Cardiff City.\n\n{{football box collapsible\n|round =  [[2007-08 Football League Cup|First Round]]\n|date = 14 August 2007\n|time = 19:45\n|team1 = [[Cardiff City F.C.|Cardiff City]]\n|score = 1-0\n|aet = yes\n|report = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/league_cup/6941839.stm\n|team2 = Brighton & Hove Albion\n|goals1 = [[Roger Johnson (footballer)|Johnson]] {{goal|110}}\n|goals2 =\n|stadium = [[Ninian Park]]\n|location = [[Cardiff]]\n|attendance = 3,726\n|referee = Trevor Kettle\n|result = L\n}}\n\n===Football League Trophy===\n{{main|2007-08 Football League Trophy}}\n\nBrighton & Hove Albion received a bye to the Southern area second round and were drawn at home to [[2007-08 Football League Two|League Two]] side [[Barnet F.C.|Barnet]]. They were knocked out in the Southern area semi-final by [[2007-08 Football League One|League One]] champions [[Swansea City]]\n\n{{football box collapsible\n|round = [[2007-08 Football League Trophy#Southern Section 2|Southern Second Round]]\n|date = 9 October 2007\n|time = 19:45\n|team1 = Brighton & Hove Albion\n|score = 2-1\n|report = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/7031370.stm\n|team2 = [[Barnet F.C.|Barnet]]\n|goals1 = [[Jake Robinson|Robinson]] {{goal|21}}<br>[[Dean Cox|Cox]] {{goal|47}}\n|goals2 = [[Adam Birchall|Birchall]] {{goal|74}}\n|stadium = [[Withdean Stadium]]\n|location = [[Brighton]]\n|attendance = 1,995\n|referee = Andy Hall\n|result = W\n}}\n\n{{football box collapsible\n|round = [[2007-08 Football League Trophy#Southern Section 3|Southern Quarter Final]]\n|date = 14 November 2007\n|time = 19:45\n|team1 = Brighton & Hove Albion\n|score = 4-1\n|report = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/7088543.stm\n|team2 = [[Cheltenham Town F.C.|Cheltenham]]\n|goals1 = [[David Martot|Martot]] {{goal|13}}<br>[[Nicky Forster|Forster]] {{goal|37||87}}<br>[[Bas Savage|Savage]] {{goal|90}}\n|goals2 = [[Paul Connor (footballer)|Connor]] {{goal|45}}\n|stadium = [[Withdean Stadium]]\n|location = [[Brighton]]\n|attendance = 2,490\n|referee = Andy Woolmer\n|result = W\n}}\n\n{{football box collapsible\n|round = [[2007-08 Football League Trophy#Southern Section 4|Southern Semi Final]]\n|date = 8 January 2008\n|time = 19:45\n|team1 = [[Swansea City]]\n|score = 1-0\n|report = https://www.11v11.com/matches/swansea-city-v-brighton-and-hove-albion-08-january-2008-279974/\n|team2 = Brighton & Hove Albion\n|goals1 = [[Darryl Duffy|Duffy]] {{goal|9}}\n|goals2 =\n|stadium = [[Liberty Stadium]]\n|location = [[Swansea]]\n|attendance = 6,066\n|referee = Jarmail Singh\n|result = L\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Brighton & Hove Albion F.C. seasons}}\n\n[[Category:Brighton & Hove Albion F.C. seasons]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football club season\n | club               = [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|Brighton & Hove Albion]]\n | pattern_la1        = _blueshoulders\n | pattern_b1         = _whitestripes\n | pattern_ra1        = _blueshoulders\n | leftarm1           = FFFFFF\n | body1              = 0000FF\n | rightarm1          = FFFFFF\n | shorts1            = FFFFFF\n | socks1             = FFFFFF\n | pattern_la2        = _white\n | pattern_b2         = _white\n | pattern_ra2        = _white\n | leftarm2           = FFFFFF\n | body2              = FFFFFF\n | rightarm2          = FFFFFF\n | shorts2            = 0000FF\n | socks2             = 0000FF\n | season             = 2007\u20132008\n | manager            = [[Dean Wilkins]]\n | league             = [[EFL League One|League One]]\n | league result      = 7th\n | chairman           = [[Dick Knight (businessman)|Dick Knight]]\n | cup1               = [[FA Cup]]\n | cup1 result        = Third Round\n | cup2               = [[Football League Cup|League Cup]]\n | cup2 result        = First Round\n | cup3               = [[Football League Trophy]]\n | cup3 result        = Southern Semi-Final\n | league topscorer   = [[Nicky Forster]] (19 goals)\n | highest attendance = 8,691 vs. [[Leeds United|Leeds]]\n | lowest attendance  = 1,995 vs [[Barnet F.C.|Barnet]]\n |prevseason=[[2006\u201307 Brighton & Hove Albion F.C. season|2006\u201307]]\n |nextseason=[[2008\u201309 Brighton & Hove Albion F.C. season|2008\u201309]]\n}}\nThe '''2007\u201308 season''' was [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|Brighton & Hove Albion]]'s 106th year in existence and second consecutive season in [[EFL League One|League One]]. Along with competing in League One, the club also participated in the [[FA Cup]] and the [[EFL Cup|League Cup]].\nThe Seagulls finished 7th in League One, missing out on the [[EFL League One play-offs#2008|promotion play-offs]] by seven points. As a result, manager [[Dean Wilkins]] was replaced by [[Micky Adams]] at the end of the season, and left the club after being offered a role as first-team coach.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11719/3702206/wilkins-snubs-brighton-offer|title=Wilkins snubs Bright offer|publisher=Sky Sports News}}</ref>\n\n==First Team Squad==\n{| class=\"wikitable style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n!style=\"background:blue; color:white; text-align:center;\"|No.\n!style=\"background:blue; color:white; text-align:center;\"|Name\n!style=\"background:blue; color:white; text-align:center;\"|Nat.\n!style=\"background:blue; color:white; text-align:center;\"|Place of birth\n!style=\"background:blue; color:white; text-align:center;\"|Date of birth\n!style=\"background:blue; color:white; text-align:center;\"|Previous club\n!style=\"background:blue; color:white; text-align:center;\"|Date joined\n!style=\"background:blue; color:white; text-align:center;\"|Notes\n|-\n| 2\n| [[Andrew Whing]]\n| {{flagicon|ENG}}\n| [[Birmingham]]\n| 20 September 1984\n| [[Coventry City F.C.|Coventry City]]\n| 7 June 2007\n|\n|-\n| 3\n| [[Kerry Mayo]]\n| {{flagicon|ENG}}\n| [[Cuckfield]]\n| 21 September 1977\n| N/A\n| 1 August 1995\n|\n|-\n| 4\n| [[